# Shekyl mission

Shekyl is privacy-preserving money designed to last. Three commitments, in this
order of precedence when they conflict:

1. **Security and quantum resilience are preconditions.** Hybrid PQC ships from
   genesis. A change that weakens the security or PQC posture is rejected,
   regardless of what it gains in privacy, usability, or features.
2. **Privacy is the product.** Every user gets the same anonymity guarantees by
   default — privacy is never a setting. A change that weakens privacy to add a
   feature of any kind other than security is rejected.
3. **The system must outlast the team.** Code is written for an unknown future
   maintainer. Every decision is evaluated against three timeframes: now, end
   of the mining era (~30 years), and the V4 lattice-only transition.

These commitments rarely conflict; they only arbitrate edge cases. When
invoking the hierarchy, name which commitment is binding and why the
alternatives were considered.

This file is the single source of truth on priority ordering. Other rules
reference this hierarchy rather than restating it. If another rule appears to
contradict this file, this file wins.
